        "description": "<p><em>Project Gotham Racing: Ferrari Edition</em> is a spin-off of the main <em>Project Gotham Racing</em> series and this release is exclusive to Zune. The game contains single-player and multiplayer races with twelve exotic sports cars licensed from Ferrari. In single-player there are regular races in 33 events in the career mode as well as time trials. In the time trials it is possible to race against ghost cars and share records with friends. Multiplayer lets the player race against up to three players in wireless network races. The racing tracks are set in London, New York and Tokyo. The game makes use of touch for controls. There are two virtual buttons, one in the bottom right (acceleration) and one in the bottom left (brake) of the screen, along with a handbrake in the middle. Steering is done by tilting the device.</p>",
